Description: 
The explorer travels to Qaanaaq, an Inuit town in the far 
north of Greenland, where he learns some of the skills that 
have enabled the native people to survive amid the harsh 
wilderness, including dog-sled driving and extracting 
water from sea ice. Hunting also remains a key part of life 
for the community, with supermarket prices for some 
staple foods set at 50 per cent more than in mainland 
Europe - but Bruce discovers the impact of global 
warming could lead to this traditional way of life dying out 
entirely.
